.SH "NAME"
disable_irq_nosync \- disable an irq without waiting
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ disable_irq_nosync('u
.BI "void disable_irq_nosync(unsigned\ int\ " "irq" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIirq\fR
.RS 4
Interrupt to disable
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Disable the selected interrupt line\&. Disables and Enables are nested\&. Unlike
\fBdisable_irq\fR, this function does not ensure existing instances of the IRQ handler have completed before returning\&.
.PP
This function may be called from IRQ context\&.
